# Commit rules

When creating a commit at the user's request, always follow this format:

**Important: All commits (title and description) MUST be written in English.**

## Commit message format

```
<short title>

<optional description>

---
Tool: <tool name, e.g. Cursor>
Agent: <agent name, e.g. Composer>
Model: <model name, e.g. claude-sonnet-4.5>

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursor@cursor.com>
```

## Example

```
feat: add PDF export support

Add PDF generation library and associated handlers.

---
Tool: Cursor
Agent: Composer
Model: claude-sonnet-4.5

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursor@cursor.com>
```

## Constraints

- **Title**: keep under 50 characters.
- **Description**: wrap each line at 72 characters maximum.
- **Tool**: the tool used for the work (e.g. Cursor, GitHub Copilot)
- **Agent**: the agent that performed the changes (e.g. Composer, Chat)
- **Model**: the language model used (e.g. claude-sonnet-4.5, gpt-4o)
- **Co-authored-by**: always include Cursor as co-author with the exact line above

When using the `git commit` command, pass this information in the message body via the `-m` option for the title and subsequent options for the body, or use a temporary message file.
